title: President Trump Announces Presidential Delegation to the Republic of Guatemala to Attend the Inauguration of His Excellency Alejandro Giammattei Falla â€“ The White House
content:
Statements & Releases			

		Foreign Policy	

Issued on:
January 8, 2020
President Donald J. Trump today announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to the Republic of Guatemala to attend the Inauguration of
His Excellency Alejandro Eduardo Giammattei Falla on January 14, 2020, in Guatemala City, Guatemala.The Honorable Wilbur L. Ross, Jr., U.S. Secretary of Commerce, will lead the delegation.Members of the Presidential Delegation:The Honorable Luis E. Arreaga, United States Ambassador to the Republic of GuatemalaThe Honorable Chad F. Wolf, Acting Secretary, U.S. Department of Homeland SecurityThe Honorable Adam S. Boehler, Chief Executive Officer, U.S. International Development Finance Corporation.
